b'' b'writes:' b'the 80-bit key will be divided between two escrow agents, each of whom' b'hold 40-bits of each key.' b'' b'presumably, the key split is so that no one group controls the privacy' b'of the key, and that it would be infeasible to illicitly gain access from' b'both agents.' b'' b'however, if one agent wishes to break the crypto without the cooperation' b'of the other agent, a 40-bit key is not going to stand in the way of a' b'brute force attack. if an agency (for example, the nsa) were to hold one' b"of the two key-halves, then i don't imagine they really need the other half of" b'the key to start listening in.' b'' b'or was that the point? <grin' b'' b'' b'(this is not to imply, at all, that i like the idea of the rest of the' b'system.)' b'--' b'lee brintle ``and so, i leave you with this final word:' b"director, project panda twang.''" 